<DOC><DOCNO> AP900120-0013 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-20-90 0524EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Vietnam-USMissing     01-20 0132</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Vietnam-US Missing,0135</SECOND><HEAD>Vietnam, US Agree To Joint Projects On Missing Soldiers</HEAD><DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Vietnamese and U.S. specialists haveagreed to conduct joint activities by the end of February toaccount for Americans reported missing from the Vietnam War, anofficial news report said.   The two sides reached agreement at a three-day meeting thatended Friday in Vietnam's capital, Hanoi, the Vietnam News Agencysaid.   No details were given in the report, seen today in Bangkok.   About 2,300 Americans are listed as missing in action from thewar, which ended in a 1975 Communist victory over the U.S.-backedSouth Vietnam government.   Joint activities in recent years have included excavation ofsites where U.S. warplanes crashed and field expeditions in whichvillagers have been asked about crashes that they witnessed.</TEXT></DOC>